</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>SCR71:v97#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="SCR71"/><meta name="dc:title" content="SCR &#xA;              71-&#xA;                CHAPTERED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div width="100%" style="text-align:center;"><div id="bill_num_title_chap"><span style="text-align:center;font-weight:bold;font-size:1.1em;font-family:'Times New Roman'; "><b>
                Senate Concurrent Resolution
              
                        No. 71</b></span></div><div style="text-align:center;padding-top: 1.0em;padding-bottom: 1.2em;" id="chap_num_title_chap"><span style="font-size:1.4em;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;">
                      CHAPTER 127</span></div></div><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to National Hospital Week. </span></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center">
                  
                  [<span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Filed with
              </span><span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Secretary of State
              </span> <span style="font-size: 13pt">July 03, 2025.
                      </span>]
                </div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">SCR 71, Allen.
                          National Hospital Week.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would designate the week of May 11, 2025, to May 17, 2025, inclusive, as National Hospital Week in California.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_2B3FE9FB-5AF6-4974-A41D-D1D8FF03C277"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, California is home to more than 450 hospitals in rural, suburban, and urban areas, that are a source of hope and healing for all in need, 24 hours a day, seven days a week, year round; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_7938C8EF-FD19-491A-85EC-B6286DCC4F53"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, California hospitals treat all who come through their doors and are havens that never close for those who need health care services; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_0631B2B8-BF35-462B-9DAC-B963669F1FD6"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, California hospitals provide life-saving and life-changing care by saving the lives of extremely premature babies, extending the lives of cancer patients and others, and improving the lives of those experiencing traumatic illness and bodily harm; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_417A2E26-5788-4C85-A83D-7EFC07F33A74"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Hospitals treat one in four Californians every year, including 15 million visits to emergency departments for critical health care services; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_BE1C8DAD-7CEF-464E-9C31-C819FF650D3E"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Hospitals deliver 400,000 babies every year in California, ensuring that birthing parents and babies are safe and cared for before, during, and after delivery; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_211FC85F-E4A0-4DD2-9291-21F1A6723DB9"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, California has the fourth highest life expectancy in the nation, with hospitals playing a critical role in the state’s health care system; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_D1E1CCEA-124A-4B22-8AF6-C7D7B5246583"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Hospitals are major economic drivers that are responsible for one million jobs and $300,000,000,000 in economic output in California; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_1C0202CB-21B1-4EA1-80D1-FC5D0C69E45D"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Hospitals, which provide safe havens for people in need of emergency care during natural disasters, were at the forefront of the disaster response during the devastating fires this year in Los Angeles; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_F5DE1479-3B36-4B61-B98D-4DC6058E5EC7"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Hospitals annually provide $10,000,000,000 in support to vulnerable populations in their communities through disease detection and prevention, wellness programs, charity care, and partnerships with community nonprofit organizations; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_0BFCE72C-DF57-48A9-8ACA-0DB7B7BB1F8C"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Hospitals are a key partner for clinics, doctors, Planned Parenthood, and others; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_A1DBAB88-9F5C-4471-8A7A-ACD619279524"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Senate of the State of California, the Assembly thereof concurring, That the Legislature hereby designates the week of May 11, 2025, to May 17, 2025, inclusive, as National Hospital Week in California; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_AB3196D0-184B-4080-A07D-0EAC785A0EF0"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Secretary of the Senate transmit copies of this resolution to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
